esthorpe, Breckland, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Besthorpe, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Besthorpe, Norfolk, England":"Besthorpe, Norfolk, England","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England","Besthrope, Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Henry","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["A perennially popular given name, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Henry de Wettenhall was born in 1390, in Besthorpe, Norfolk, England, his father, Thomas Whetenhall, was 40 and his mother, Margaret Warner, was 30. He married Cicilie Spayne in 1429, in Norfolk, England. They were the parents of at least 4 sons. He died in 1450, in his hometown, at the age of 60."},"et":{"1390–1450":"1390–1450","1403–1434":"1403–1434","1430–Male":"1430–Surnud","1431–Male":"1431–S